16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 301B of Title 44, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
21 fund for the Oklahoma Military Department to be designated the "Base
22 Infrastructure Needs and Development - Technology Revolving Fund",
23 which may also be cited as "BIND – Technology Fund". The fund shall
24 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2518 Page 1

1 shal l consist of all monies directed for deposit to the fund by law.
2 All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby
3 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
4 Military Department for the purpose established in subsection B of
5 this section. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon
6 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
7 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
8 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
9 B. There is hereby established within the Oklahoma Military
10 Department the "Base Infrastructure Needs and Development –
11 Technology Program", which may also be cited as the "BIND –
12 Technology Program". The Department shall utilize funds from the
13 BIND – Technology Fund created in subsection A of this section,
14 alone or in combination with other available funding, to make
15 infrastructure investments, including, but not limited to, the
16 purchase of licenses and software associated with military
17 simulation training, that will either:
18 1. Decrease the likelihood of military base and other military
19 infrastructure closures in this state; or
20 2. Increase the likelihood of military base and other military
21 infrastructure expansions in this state.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
